cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of translating videos into natural language, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of computational linguistic models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a novel approach for learning higher level representations, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of classifiers, which could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with videos, which could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
